cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SY 

The paper proposes algorithms for learning fair decision-making policies for Markov decision processes (MDPs), which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses fairness constraints and simulations on a loan applicant MDP, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper deals with the dynamics of MDPs, which could be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
